                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/491: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-02T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 2, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 6.37 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2924. Your 1032, March 8, 4 p.m.,<note n="57" xml:id="d208fn57">Not
                        printed.</note> and our 2863, June 28, 10 p.m. Confidential. Yanez states he
                    intends sail about July 20th for the United States. His conversation seemed to
                    indicate Chilean Government would be loath to submit Tacna-Arica question to
                    League of Nations, but favors negotiations with Peru through the medium of the
                    good offices of our Government only.</p>
                <p>Yanez engaged at present with economic duties of his mission. He visited Creusot
                    works this week presumably for the purpose of placing orders. Lansing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
